    "client_msg_id": "03655b81-21ba-4e69-892f-863f3bc5edb1",
    "type": "message",
    "text": "Direct manipulation of moving something on the screen has almost zero value in programming. That is not where bugs come from; that is mostly aesthetic iteration, which is one of the easiest parts of programming. Sure it saves a little bit of time, but since debugging is 80%+ of programming, how much has been saved by direct manipulation of an existing graphic?. Trying to correct an order-of-initialization issue can take huge amounts of time, and that is something that apparently graphical manipulation is very weak at fixing.",
