    "type": "message",
    "text": "hey <@UEQ6M68H0> good notes, thanks; I agree with the debugging not being even touched here (besides the state tree visualisation below the canvas), there's few different examples getting more complex in the examples section, but I was making them to resemble processing / p5 examples; I while I would agree that aesthetic iteration is _easy_ it is a huge part of generative / art projects — I sometimes spend half the time building a system, and then second half exploring which outputs from all the little \"knob tweaking\" I like (I did a bit of research on automating that here: <https://szymonkaliski.com/projects/parametrium/>)",
